         <abstract id="aspace_d01b852b89975a616044643418efe184">Political activist; nurse; owner of
            Internationalist Book Store in Chapel Hill, N.C. Sheldon was murdered in the store on
            February 21, 1991. Drafts of Sheldon's speeches, articles, diary and notes; news
            clippings; printed materials; and transcripts of trials and FBI files. Materials relate
            chiefly to his political activism as a draft resister in 1968; a visit to China in the
            1970s, including slides; work with the Communist Workers Party in the 1970s and the
            Green Party in the 1980s; union organizing at Cone Mills Textile plant in the 1970s; and
            various Palestine issues in the 1980s.</abstract>
